pageContext.claim: “'Democrats suffered crushing down-ballot loss across America.' @nytimes. This is true. All statehouses won, and in Washington we did great. So I led this great charge, and I'm the only one that lost? No, it doesn't work that way.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump never achieved better than 50 percent approval as president, so there may have been many people willing to support Republicans at lower-level offices but could not vote to re-elect Trump.
